  cantor[n] = yscale(1/2)*xscale(1/3)*(cantor[n - 1])--cantor[0]--shift((2/3,1/2))*yscale(1/2)*xscale(1/3)*(cantor[n - 1]);
}

draw(cantor[10],red);
draw((0,0)--(1,0));
draw((0,0)--(0,1));
[/asy]

For reference, the function $f(x)$ is called the Cantor function.  It is also known as the Devil's Staircase.
